<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-205-117 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 439 248</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  March 4 1991 n341 p8(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>User issues: service local competition. (telephone companies)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Bushaus, Dawn.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Many customers of telephone companies consider customer service ascritical as price in selecting service providers.andP;  Many are readyto see some competition in the local loop, according to a surveyreleased by Andersen Consulting.andP;  Over 200 middle-market telephonecompany users with annual telecommunications budgets ranging from$50,000 to $1 million took part.andP;  Results indicated that 45percent of telephone company users would change local carriersright away given the choice.andP;  Some 60 percent favor competition inthe local loop.andP;  Virtually all considered customer service animportant criteria in vendor selection.andP;  Approximately 70 percentare willing to pay more for good service.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Telephone CompaniesCompetitionCustomer RelationsTelecommunications ServicesUser NeedsMarket Analysis.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>